==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The process by which a new word, X, is formed from another, Y, by removing a portion of Y that is falsely perceived to be a ''[[bound morpheme]]'' attached to a ''[[root morpheme]]''.


===Examples===

''[[burgle]]'': a back-formation from the noun ''[[burglar]]'', formed by removing the ending ''-ar'', as if ''burglar'' were an [[agent noun]] formed by adding this ending to the verb ''burgle''.

''[[edit]]'': a back-formation from the noun editor.

''[[flammable]]'': a back formation from the adjective ''[[inflammable]]''.


